ProcessOutput dataclass

class process_output.ProcessOutput(process_state, current_event_result, messages, picking_robot_commands, fastening_robot_commands, next_recommended_action, valid_assembly_positions)

Bases: object

Output dataclass for neatly outputting the return for handle_motion_event().

process_state

Updated process state after a motion event.

Type: ProcessState

current_event_result

Evaluated information on the current event. Can be either AssemblyEventResult or PickEventResult depending on the evaluated motion event.

Type: Union [AssemblyEventResult, PickEventResult]

messages

A tuple containing str messages. These messages confirm a motion event or an error. For easily consumable feedback for the input motion event.

Type: tuple [str]

picking_robot_commands

tuple containing robot command codes for the picking robot

See Picking Robot Command Codes for reference.

Determined in: determine_picking_robot_commands()

Type: tuple

fastening_robot_commands

tuple containing robot command codes for the fastening robot

See Fastening Robot Command Codes for reference.

Determined in: determine_fastening_robot_commands()

Type: tuple

next_recommended_action

Next recommended worker action (Place part with ID x at pos (x,x)) See parameter next_recommended_action.

Type: Action

valid_assembly_positions

set containing valid assembly Pos for the part ID that was picked.

Type: set [Pos]
